when we want to set default editor for git,
at first we need a command on terminal that can open the editor.
(code is standard for visual studio
 idea is standard for intellij)

we should set this command first,
when we execute a command on terminal,
the shell look some folders that introduce this command (like /usr/local/bin)
(the PATH VARIABLE store the address that we want put these files)
the Intellij related folder is not add to this path automatically,
we should put it there we call this as:
"Create Command-line Launcher"

1.at first we need the path address
  that stores the exe file of our app (our editor)
  we can find it from the intellij UI
  (Tools--->create command line launcher):
  /Applications/IntelliJ IDEA.app/Contents/MacOS

2.now we put the address on the PATH (where shell explore for commands):
  export PATH="/Applications/IntelliJ IDEA.app/Contents/MacOS:$PATH"

Note: now when we write "idea" on terminal
      our intellij will be opened

Note: this folder have the standard name for command ("idea" for intellij)
      the visual studio the standard name is "code"
      it's like "git", when we install git, it automatically add
      this to PATH, so we will access to "git" as command
      on intellij we should do it manually

Note: we can set any name for this:
      sudo ln -s "/Applications/IntelliJ IDEA.app/Contents/MacOS/idea" /usr/local/bin/intellij
      he create "SYMBOLIC LINK",
      in the directory of /usr/local/bin (shell check this directory by default)
      he create a file with the name of "intellij"
      that inside this file we have a link to:
      /Applications/IntelliJ IDEA.app/Contents/MacOS/idea

Note: PATH VARIABLE, is an environment variable
      it store all the addresses that shell wants to check
      we add our new address there
      addresses separate by ":"
      we can see the addresses (value of this environment variable)
      by "echo $PATH" on terminal
      :/bin:/usr/sbin:/sbin:/var/run/com.apple.security.cryptexd/codex.system/bootstrap/usr/local/bin
